      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "@MarcoFalke I was simply thinking about the case where a future call site pass user- or attacker controlled input in the form of an HRP to `Encode(â¦)`.\r\n\r\nPerhaps that is farfetched but returning success in some form (say using `true` or returning a non-empty string) instead of `assert`:ing would also be consistent with  [`bech32_encode(â¦)` in the C implementation](https://github.com/sipa/bech32/blob/2b0aac650ce560fb2b2a2bebeacaa5c87d7e5938/ref/c/segwit_addr.c#L59).\r\n\r\nAnother alternative would be to simply lowercase the HRP as @fanquake suggested.\r\n\r\nGenerally I think we should avoid `assert`:ing on input that might be directly user- or attacker controlled to avoid unnecessary DoS vectors :-)",
